When we learn how to fix inner and outer corner beveling under the condition of not allowing bevel geo info to go through, we actually learn a middle way method between beveling and fencing.  

In many cases, bevel geo info are not allowed to go through. We prefer using beveling and fix the corner manually over fencing. The reason is fencing technique uses insert edge loop, and there is little control of the extra geo. If we don't want to maintain volume, we just want it round and smooth, then we need to clean up all those extra geo manually, which takes way more time than fixing the corner. 

This is a mesh using beveling without letting the geo go through. 

And we would have corner issues at the red circle area.
